wwpLeosTrafficProfileMIB.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileMIB

revisions.description: Added classifier mode under the wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortEntry. Added wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdUntaggedState under WwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEntry

Added modes hierarchicalVlan(12), hierarchicalPort(13) to wwpLeosTrafficProfileMode under wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortEntry. Added wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDefaultProfile, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDrop, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdParentIndex, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdChildMode under wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdTable

Added modes stdVlanDot1dPri, stdVlanIpp, stdDscp to wwpLeosTrafficProfileMode under wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortEntry. Added objects wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCbs, wwpLeosTrafficProfileEbs, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDscpRemarkPolicy, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdFixedDscp to wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEntryTable

Added wwpLeosTrafficProfileMeterPoolTable under wwpLeosTrafficProfile wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIndx mib object value has been changed from 1..32 to 1..64 Added wwpLeosTrafficProfileMeterPool mib object under wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortEntry.

Added additional trafficPorfileMode stdDscp. Profile Index changed for following mib object from 1 through 8 to 1 through 32 wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIndx, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dTpProfile, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIpPrecToProfile, wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdPhbToProfile. Added new wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDscpTable. Added new wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdVlanTable.
added value in cascaded enumerations for deprecated values
changed description of entries relating to cascaded profiling
deprecated all entries related to cascaded traffic profiling.
The MIB module for the WWP leos traffic profiling specific information.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileGlobalState.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileGlobalState
wwpLeosTrafficProfileGlobalState.description: Setting this object to 'enabled' will enable traffic profile globally. Setting this object to 'disabled' will disable traffic profile globally.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileGlobalMeterProvisio.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileGlobalMeterProvisioningState
wwpLeosTrafficProfileGlobalMeterProvisio.description: Setting this object to 'pir' will allow meters to be provisioned in pir. Setting this object to 'eir' will allow meters to be provisioned in eir.

wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortTable.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortTable
wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortTable.description: A table of traffic profile port entries.

wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortEntry.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortEntry
wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortEntry.description: A traffic profile entry in the wwpLeosTrafficProfilePortTable.

wwpLeosTrafficProfilePort.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfilePort
wwpLeosTrafficProfilePort.description: This object specifies the port number also used as index in the table.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileAdminState.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileAdminState
wwpLeosTrafficProfileAdminState.description: Setting this object to 'enabled' will administratively enable traffic profiling on the given port. Setting this object to 'disabled' will administratively disable traffic profiling on the given port.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileOperState.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileOperState
wwpLeosTrafficProfileOperState.description: This object specifies operational state of the traffic profiling for a given port on the device.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileMode.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileMode
wwpLeosTrafficProfileMode.description: This object specifies the mode of traffic profiling for a given port.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformCascadedP.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformCascadedProfile
wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformCascadedP.description: This object specifies that the device should map non-conformance traffic ingressing on a given port to cascaded profile specified by wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformCascadedProfile. This object will become effective only if device is running in cascaded profile mode. This object will be set to drop if using on a device that does not have cascaded-profiling

wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformStdProfil.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformStdProfile
wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformStdProfil.description: This object specifies that the device should map non-conformance traffic ingressing on a given port to standard profile specified by wwpLeosTrafficProfileNonConformStdProfile. This object will become effective only if device is running in standard profile mode.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpCascadedProfile.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpCascadedProfile
wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpCascadedProfile.description: This object specifies that the device should map ARP frames ingressing on a given port to cascaded profile specified by wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpCascadedProfile. This object will be set to bypass if using on a device that does not have cascaded-profiling.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpStdProfile.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpStdProfile
wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpStdProfile.description: This object specifies that the device should map ARP frames ingressing on a given port to standard profile specified by wwpLeosTrafficProfileArpStdProfile. This object will become effective only if device is running in standard profile mode.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileMeterPool.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileMeterPool
wwpLeosTrafficProfileMeterPool.description: This object specifies the Meter Pool Index for a port.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileClassifierMode.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileClassifierMode
wwpLeosTrafficProfileClassifierMode.description: This object specifies how narrow or wide we classify traffic to a port's meters.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedTable.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedTable
wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedTable.description: A table of cascaded traffic profile entries. To create an entry in this table the following criteria must be met. - All indexes must be specified. - wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedCir must be specified - if wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedPir is not specified or is specified and is < wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedCir then device will make wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedPir = wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedCir - wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedStatus must be set to createandgo

wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedEntry.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedEntry
wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedEntry.description: A cascaded traffic profile entry in the wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedTable.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedIndx.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedIndx
wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedIndx.description: This object is used as index in the table and it represents profile index which can be 1 or 2 or 3.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedCir.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedCir
wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedCir.description: This object specifies the cir associated with a given cascaded traffic profile. Units are kbps.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedPir.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedPir
wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedPir.description: This object specifies the pir associated with a given cascaded traffic profile. Units are kbps.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedStatus.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedStatus
wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createandgo' along with wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedCir and wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedPir will result in creating an cascaded traffic profile entry. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdTable.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdTable
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdTable.description: A table of Std traffic profile entries. To create entry in this table following criteria must be met. - All indexes must be specified. - wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCir must be specified - if wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdPir is not specified or is specified and is < wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCir then device will make wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdPir = wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCir - wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdStatus must be set to createandgo

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEntry.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEntry
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEntry.description: A standard traffic profile entry in the wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdTable.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIndx.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIndx
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIndx.description: This object is used as index in the table and it represents profile index which can be 1 through 64.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCir.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCir
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCir.description: This object specifies the cir associated with a given standard traffic profile.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdPir.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdPir
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdPir.description: This object specifies the pir associated with a given standard traffic profile.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdName.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdName
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdName.description: The name associated with this profile. This must be unique per port. The name does not have to be set on create. However, when updating the name, it must have some value - zero-string not support.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdStatus.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdStatus
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdStatus.description: Setting this object to 'createandgo' along with wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCir and or wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdPir will result in creating an standard traffic profile entry. Setting this object to 'destroy' will delete the entry from the table.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdVlan.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdVlan
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdVlan.description: This object specifies the VLAN associated with a profile.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCbs.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCbs
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdCbs.description: This object specifies the Commited burst size associated with a given standard traffic profile.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEbs.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEbs
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEbs.description: This object specifies the Excess burst size associated with a given standard traffic profile.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDscpRemarkPolicy.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDscpRemarkPolicy
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDscpRemarkPolicy.description: Leave => Don't remark the frame. Fixed => Remark the DSCP of a frame with the fixed-dscp value for IP frames which classify to the Traffic Profile

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdFixedDscp.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdFixedDscp
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdFixedDscp.description: Fixed DSCP value to use for frames classifying to a Traffic Profile when the dscp-remark-policy id 'Fixed

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdUnsetVlan.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdUnsetVlan
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdUnsetVlan.description: Setting This object to unset(1) unsets the VLAN associated with a profile. This object returns a value of none(0) on get.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDefaultProfile.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDefaultProfile
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDefaultProfile.description: Setting this object to true(1) during createAndGo(4) will create Tier-1 default profile.

wwpLeosTrafficeProfileStdDrop.name: wwpLeosTrafficeProfileStdDrop
wwpLeosTrafficeProfileStdDrop.description: Setting this value to true causes metering to cease and all traffic to drop.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdParentIndex.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdParentIndex
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdParentIndex.description: This mib object is set when creating Child traffic profile to specify the parent index

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdChildMode.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdChildMode
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdChildMode.description: When the port mode is hierarchical-vlan, then the valid child-modes are dot1dPri, ipprec, dscp. When the port mode is hierarchical-port then the valid childModes is dot1dPri, ipprec, dscp and vlan(4).

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdStatsMonitor.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdStatsMonitor
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdStatsMonitor.description: To disable stats collection, set this object to off(2). To enable stats collection, set this object to on(1).

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdUntaggedState.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdUntaggedState
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdUntaggedState.description: To enable this profile to match untagged traffic set this to on(1). To disable, set to off(2)

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdVs.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdVs
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdVs.description: The virtual-switch name associated with this profile. The virtual-switch name must exist before using it as a profile classifier.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdRemarkColorPolic.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdRemarkColorPolicy
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdRemarkColorPolic.description: This sets the profile's color remarking policy at the meter output.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdRemarkRcosPolicy.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdRemarkRcosPolicy
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdRemarkRcosPolicy.description: This sets the profile's rcos remarking policy based on meter color.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdYellowRemarkRcos.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdYellowRemarkRcos
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdYellowRemarkRcos.description: This sets the profile's rcos remarking policy based on meter color.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdGreenRemarkRcos.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdGreenRemarkRcos
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdGreenRemarkRcos.description: This sets the profile's rcos remarking policy based on meter color.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIngressColorAwar.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIngressColorAware
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdIngressColorAwar.description: This sets the profile's meter ingress color awareness.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEir.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEir
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdEir.description: This object specifies the eir associated with a given standard traffic profile. Sets/Gets on this are only valid when the global meter-provisioning mode is set to eir. All other times it will be ignored and return 0

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dTable.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dTable
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dTable.description: A table of Std dot1d traffic profile entries. To create entry in the table following criteria must be met - set wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dStatus to 'createandgo'. - set wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dToProfile to valid profile. To delete entry set wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dStatus to destroy.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dEntry.name: wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dEntry
wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dEntry.description: A standard dot1d traffic profile entry in the wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dTable.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1d.description: This object specifies the dot1d priority for the associated standard profile entry in the wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dTable table.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dToProfile.description: This object specifies the profile to which wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1d must be mapped to.

To delete entry set wwpLeosTrafficProfileStdDot1dStatus to destroy.

wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedStatsEntry.description: A cascaded traffic profile entry in the wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedStatsTable.

To create entry in this table following criteria must be met. - All indexes must be specified. - wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedGlobalDot1d,wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedGlobalIpPrec and wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedGlobalDscp may be specified. - wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedGlobalName may be specified. - wwpLeosTrafficProfileCascadedGlobalStatus must be set to createandgo
